20/12/2005
TIRANA, Albania -- Defence Minister Fatmir Mediu says Albania hopes to be invited to join NATO at the Alliance's summit in 2008, Speaking to reporters Monday (19 December) after a meeting with NATO's Supreme Commander in Europe, US General James Jones, Mediu said his government has adopted a plan for reforms to that end.
Jones reiterated NATO's commitment to helping candidate countries meet required standards but refused to discuss specific dates.
He also met with President Alfred Moisiu and Prime Minister Sali Berisha.
(Albanian News - 20/12/05;
AFP, Albanian President Web site - 19/12/05)
